wikipedia_page.main: John Wyndham Hamilton McCulloch (4 December 1894 – 21 October 1915) was an English first-class cricketer active 1913–14 who played for Middlesex. He was born in Calcutta; died in Bailleul, Nord, France during World War I.

response: *John McCulloch (MP) (1842–1912), British Member of Parliament for Glasgow St Rollox, 1885–1886
